.Dd April 14, 2026
.Dt NOD 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm nod
.Nd suckless notification daemon
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl v
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a minimal notification daemon for X11 that implements enough of the
Desktop Notifications Specification 1.2 over D-Bus to work with
.Xr notify-send 1
and any application that emits standard notifications.
.Pp
.Nm
claims the well-known name
.Pa org.freedesktop.Notifications
on the session bus and displays notifications as override-redirect
X11 windows rendered with Xft.
Only one notification daemon can own that name at a time.
.Pp
Configuration is compile-time only: edit
.Pa config.h
and rebuild.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl v
Print version and exit.
.El
.Sh INTERACTION
.Bl -tag -width "Left-click "
.It Sy Left-click
Invoke the
.Dq default
action if the notification registered one, then dismiss.
.It Sy Right-click
Dismiss only. Never invoke action.
.It Sy Timeout
Auto-dismiss after the notification's expire time.
.El
.Sh SUPPORTED HINTS
.Bl -tag -width "urgency (byte)  "
.It Sy urgency No (byte)
0 = low, 1 = normal, 2 = critical.
Selects colors and default timeout from
.Pa config.h .
.El
.Pp
All other hints are ignored.
HTML/pango markup in
.Sy summary
and
.Sy body
is stripped; only plain text is rendered.
.Sh CAPABILITIES
.Nm
advertises
.Sy body
and
.Sy actions
via
.Sy GetCapabilities .
It does not advertise
.Sy body-markup ,
.Sy body-images ,
.Sy icon-static ,
.Sy persistence ,
or
.Sy sound .
.Sh SIGNALS
.Bl -tag -width "SIGTERM "
.It Sy SIGINT , SIGTERM
Clean up windows, release the D-Bus name, exit.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "config.def.h "
.It Pa config.h
Per-user appearance, timeouts, position, stacking.
Copied from
.Pa config.def.h
on first build.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Start from
.Pa ~/.xinitrc
before the window manager:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
nod &
exec dwm
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr nod-send 1 ,
.Xr notify-send 1 ,
.Xr gdbus 1
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Matteo Merola
.Sh BUGS
Only one default action is respected;
other action keys are ignored.
No icon, sound, or markup support by design.
